        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the .NET Framework version 2.0, the core XML classes have been enhanced to include type support features.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Xml.XmlReader&gt;</ph>, <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter&gt;</ph>, and <ph id="ph3">&lt;xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator&gt;</ph> classes include type support features including the ability to convert between XML Schema types and common language runtime (CLR) types.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the .NET Framework version 2.0, the <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Xml.XmlReader&gt;</ph>, <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter&gt;</ph>, and <ph id="ph3">&lt;xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator&gt;</ph> classes have been enhanced to include type support features.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Xml.XmlReader&gt;</ph> and <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator&gt;</ph> classes each include a <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>SchemaInfo<ept id="p1">**</ept> property that returns the schema information on a node.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>ReadContentAs<ept id="p1">**</ept> and <bpt id="p2">**</bpt>ReadElementContentAs<ept id="p2">**</ept> and methods on the <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Xml.XmlReader&gt;</ph> class read a text value and convert it to a CLR value in a single method call.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter.WriteValue%2A&gt;</ph> method on the <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter&gt;</ph> class converts a CLR type to an XML Schema type when writing out XML.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>ValueAs<ept id="p1">**</ept> and <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.TypedValue%2A&gt;</ph> properties on the <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator&gt;</ph> class return a node value and convert it to a CLR value in a single method call.</source>
        </trans-unit>
